    - Businesses operating during the pandemic, "thank you" review #3* -

    Who: Simsim Outstanding Shawarma

    What:  is offering pick-up and delivery through @postmates @ubereats @grubhub

    When: Operating hours. Please call to confirm the business is indeed facilitating either pickup, delivery, or both.

    Specials: "We are all in this together! Let Simsim do the weekend cooking for you with our Togetherness Pack + 2 rolls of toilet paper per order!"

    Shawarma Togetherness Pack - includes 4 shawarmas, falafel, our signature side plate, garlic sauce and tahini sauce!

    Kebab Togetherness Pack - includes 2 Chicken Skewers, 2 Ground Beef & Lamb Skewers, Our Signature Side Plate, Fattoush Salad, Spiced Arabic Rice and sauces! Carmel Mt only." - sourced on 3/21 from Simsim's Facebook page.

    Additional: "Pick up a your favorite Simsim meal or have it delivered right to your door today! Check out UberEats for our special offers and more! Place your takeout order at eatsimsim.com/orderonline or give us a call at Simsim Carmel Mountain (858)618-5948 or Simsim Clairemont Mesa (858)430-6717" - sourced from Simsim's Facebook page.

    - *As long as the world is in an unpredictable place with the coronavirus dictating our lives and schedules, I'm going to review businesses who are still operating to provide us some sense of normalcy, and this is one of those reviews. My reviews will be 100% positive when clearly indicated with the "Businesses during the pandemic" header and footer. Feel free to steal the format and do the same for the hard working businesses that you come across. -

    5/8/2019Previous review

    Okay, listen up, San Diego. If you've dined at Simsim, someday you're going to be a part of a very exclusive group of people that can say, "I told you so." Why? Well, let me detail exactly that!

    The second you walk through the doors you'll realize that though this is a single location, mom and pop, owner working the counter type of place, it's ready for world domination. Yes, the decor, the branding, the flow, the process, the food... Simsim is sure to scale. Don't be surprised when there is a Simsim location in just about every city, but rather join the club of: "I told you so."

    How about the food? The shawarma is insane. I'm particularly partial to the chicken wrap and my favorite part is that it's not weighed down with filler like lettuce and tomatoes. Only the really good stuff here and when served with a big ol' plate of fries it's an incredibly satisfying meal. My wife loves the bowls over the wraps but there is no loser in this equation as they're both delicious and extremely affordable as well.

    You're certainly going to have to sip on something while you dine and I'll dish up two suggestions for you. First: The hibiscus lemonade is out of this world. I'm not joking. I dream about this lemonade and when I'm within Simsim's four walls I power through several cups - a must order with any item. Second: The milk tea, served out of tradition is a great way to end your meal and the best part is that it's complimentary and self-serve. Have one or two and thank me later.

    There you have it. Simsim is poised for success and mark my words when we see their beautiful storefronts dotting the map across the country. It's not if, but when, and one again, I can't wait to be someone that can say, "I told you so..." So, wanna join my club?

    A big thank you to Simsim and the staff for staying open with the current pandemic. During this time, SimSim is offering a special Shawrma togetherness pack. For $55 a family of can enjoy:  - 2 Simple Chicken & Garlic Shawarmas - 2 Authentic Meat & Tahini Shawarmas - Signature Side Plate w/ pita bread - Side of our Falafel - Garlic & Tahini Sauces - 2 Rolls of Toilet Paper (if you dont want it, we will donate them to charity). No substitutions or modifications.

    Online ordering for pick up or for delivery with postmates and ubereats is available (eatsimsim.brinkposmobile…). You can set the time for when you want to pick up your food!

    Since my household did not need 4 shawarmas and extra toilet paper, we ordered the Honest Chicken Bowl and Humble Meat Bowl (beef/lamb) for pick up. You can customize the orders on the website selecting between rice, crushed wheat bulgur, salad or a mix, and additional toppings if desired. We've been to Simsim several times before and this seems to be our standard order.

    Picking up was easy and contact free. Our food was placed into the reusable black containers, readily bagged and prepaid through the online system. Delicious as ever with generous portions and extra sauces for us to enjoy. I love the chicken as it's always juicy, tender, and flavorful. Certainly one of our neighborhood favorites and I'll definitely continue to support this local business.

    I was so, so excited to try this place since they seemed to have some unique Mediterranean items on their menu. Unfortunately it was a let down all around. I ordered directly from their website for takeout due to covid. I ordered the simsim wrap asking for the fattoush salad as a side instead of fries. My partner ordered the chicken shawarma fries and wanted tahini and pomegranate molasses sauce on the side. When we got our order home, they gave me fries instead of salad and the fries didn't have any pomegranate sauce. Not a great start.

    As for the quality of the food. Really hit and miss. My wrap was no longer crispy (which is somewhat expected from it being takeout) but the flavor was really good. The chicken and garlic sauces were also tasty as well. However, everything else was pretty meh. The pomegranate seeds didn't add that much pop in flavor, I didn't taste any potatoes in the wrap and the overall components together were very one note. For myself and my partner, the BIGGEST disappointment was the fries. Flavorless and not crispy. They tasted like they were made long before our order. Especially for his dish when the main component was the fries, it leads to a pretty dissapointing dish.

    I would actually have given two stars but bumped it up one since they're open during covid right now. I would be willing to give them a try again since so many people have said great things but would definitely wait till I can eat in.

    We had the pleasure of trying Simsim's Outstanding Shawarma and bowls during Yelp Elite Week. Their bowls and shawarma are packed with flavor, halal certified and they've also got vegan options.

    Don't pass up the Hibiscus Lemonade with a delightful note of rose water! You'll thank me later.

    I had their Indulge bowl that comes with both carved  chicken (skin, breast and land carved beef and lamb. The juicy meat sits atop a bed of fried pita chips, garbanzo beans, mint, parsley and slivered almonds and is topped with tomato and tahini sauce! Come hungry if you order this- it's very filling!

    My boyfriend got the Simple Chicken and Garlic Shawarma and the spicy garlic sauce was soooo good! The wrap itself was a perfect thickness and their pita is made in house, as well as all their tasty sauces. They have a Smokey baba ganoush that accompanies the entrees well.

    They're all super friendly and super helpful if it's your first time trying g shawarma. And don't forget to try their complimentary cardamom black and milk tea by the soda fountain.

    This place still has that brand new feel. I like that upon entering, Simsim exiles freshness.

    The food IS fresh!

    My favorites:

    Falafel: just enough crunchiness on the outside balanced with fluffiness on the outside. The tahini sauce it comes with whether as a wrap or as a sole appetizer is a tangy accompaniment.

    Baba Ganoush: my staple to determine if I will be returning to a restaurant of similar cuisine. Simsim's version is one of the better ones! The freshness of the eggplant is brought out by the bell peppers in this appetizer.

    Muhammara: pretty nice flavor, although not something I am used to. I usually get my Muhammara from restaurants in Glendale or made by one of my friends but I think you should give it a try.

    I would go back for 3 tubs of Baba Ganoush all for myself, haha!

    Had the chance to talk to the owner/chef and hear his story about this restaurant and what he would like to do with it.  And judging by the quality of his food I think he is on his way to achieving it.

    I'm no connoisseur of falafels by any mean so take this for what you like but Sim Sim's falafels are the best I've had. They have the right  crunch with the right moisture and flavor.  Not the dry, over fried, underseasoned patties things at other places.  

    The menu holds true to the owners culture but the have found a way to incorporate western favorite dishes (french fries) into their menu.  And doing so with portion sizes that are unseen at the prices they offer.  It may not be the least expensive menu but it definitely is the best bang for your buck option when taking into account quality, portion, taste, and price.  

    Do yourself a favor and check this place out.

    Awesome.

    This clean and very well kept this place is a nice addition to the hood. You walk in and order up front then they give you a little light up/buzzer thing to claim your food when it's ready. While perusing the menu, the manager approached and asked if we'd like him to run through the options with us, we took him up on the offer. He explained the entire menu and even offered us a plate of various samples which we accepted. It contained chicken, beef/lamb, hummus baba ganoush and a few other tasty options. This sampler could've been an appetizer in itself and was a very nice touch.

    Ultimately, we went with a SimSim shawarma (chicken and pomegranate) and a spicy meat (beef/lamb with spicy tahini). Both came lightly grilled in flat bread with a side of fries. Perfectly cooked, just the right amount of sauce and veggies and seasoned to perfection, these guys know what they're doing. Btw, the fries were pretty killer too.

    Great service, great food. Worth checking out.

    In the past year I've grown to really enjoy Mediterranean food and have made it a mission to try all the good ones in San Diego (there are so many)! Simsim's is definitely one that I would come back to!

    5/5 Honest Chicken Bowl - Good portions! Not sure what bulgur rice was, but it was hearty in texture and full of flavor. Definitely recommend trying something new by getting whatever choice of rice they have rather than the regular rice. Vegetables were fresh, chicken was well cooked and well seasoned, and the pomegranate seeds add a nice touch. Tzatziki sauce came in abundance, and I was able to get tahini on the side for free. The tahini was super nutty and creamy and delicious!

    Overall, I thoroughly enjoyed my food & the service here. I would say that the flavors are more indulgent than some other Mediterranean places, such as Tahini on Clairemont Mesa. But this is not to say one is better than the other! I love them both! I would go to Simsim's if I wanted something more hearty, rich and comforting; and Tahini if I wanted something lighter, fresher and more pickle-y.

    My friend got the Spicy shawrma wrap and really liked his food too :) Excited to come back and try more items.

    Side note: there is complimentary tea!
